Task Description:
-----------------
Create the K8s EKS,further you have to do the deployment of the Nginx application and 
access the application outside the cluster.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Steps:
------
1. Create an Ec2 instance
Name - K8s-task
AMI- ubuntu

2. Install awscli, kubectl, eksctl 

--------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.1 ---------------

3. create a cluster using eksctl in aws eks service.

cluster name - task-cluster
region - ap-south-1
nodegroup name - linux-N-grp
nodetype - t3.medium
node count - 2
fully managed.

command:
eksctl create cluster \
> --name task-cluster \
> --region ap-south-1 \
> --nodegroup-name linux-N-grp \
> --node-type t3.medium \
> --nodes 2 \
>  --managed

--------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.2 ---------------

4.Verified cluster creation in aWS console under eks dashboard & in terminal 

commands :
 kubectl get nodes

5. create a manifest file to deploy a nginx application 

image - nginx:latest
replicas - 2
container port - 80 

Commands:
kubectl get deploy
kubectl apply -f deploy-manifest.yaml

6. Create a service manifest.yaml file to connect to the application outside of the cluster.

service type - LoadBalancer
Port - 80

commands:
kubectl get svc
kubectl apply -f svc-manifest.yaml

--------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.3 ---------------

7. Get the External IP address that the service uses

command:
kubectl get svc nginx-service -> displays the External IP - DNS 

8. Paste the External IP to the browser to visit the default Nginx welcome page to verify,
that the nginx Application is up and Running.

--------- Please refer to task-2-Screenshot-2.4 ---------------
